content.detailedDescription:
I pulled into a parking spot at zehr's in orillia, on earlier today (sept 23/15). it was roughly 12noon. i was looking at the sky out the windshield when i saw a commercial aircraft that looked to be at full altitude leaving a short dbl contrail behind it heading from an easterly direction  to the west. just behind the commercial craft was a smaller object appearing sphere like also leaving a contrail much shorter, a single trail and much thinner than the commercial craft. at first the object was roughly 3-4 of the commercial craft length behind and to the right of the contrail. it seemed to slow allowing the gap to become larger (6-8 commercial craft lengths),although it maintained the same flight path. i got out of my vehicle and continued to watch. it almost looked as if it had momentarily stopped. suddenly it sped up and shot forward toward the plane back to 3-4 commercial craft lengths and it darted from the right side on the contrail through it and to the left side seemingly sideways to get there so quickly . the object became much brighter several times during the sighting - perhaps sun glare?
i looked down for a fraction of a second and then back but it was gone. the commercial aircraft continued on its course but the object had completely vanished. not even a trace of contrail from it. sighting lasted roughly 4 minutes i believe. i was a little stunned to be honest.  was it a jet fighter or a chaser jet? i wondered if that could be it so i did a little reading upon my return home. from that reading i learned that safety regulations prevent chaser jets from flying too close to larger aircraft or flying directly in its emissions wake.....So what was it?
thank you for your time.
sherri collins
p.S. i do not own a cell phone i would have taken a million pictures!
there may have been other witnesses that saw it because i was standing in the parking lot looking up to the sky at it.
content.summary: Looked out vehicle window saw commerical aircraft leaving dbl contrail then saw much smaller object to right of trail

content.detailedDescription: For the past year my friend and i have been looking up in the sky and noticing a lot of activity. at first it looked like many stars that we were gazing at and then we started to notice them moving around almost like a school of fish at times, blinking, or buzzing around. at first it seemed like one or two ufos but it was almost like they new we were looking and they started to reveal theirselves more and more. lately we have been seeing more dramatic events. like brighter closer ufos and or colorful blinking ufos. most of the time they hover and then erratically buzz around in the sky then hover some more and so forth. early this morning we decided to record it. we focused in a bright red star-like ufo. once we started recording it, it started moving around and changing from one color to the next of the rainbow. but what was more amazing is that the camera was picking up on many smaller blue lights or ufos flying allover the surrounding area of the colorful ufo that our naked eye was not seeing. i recorded a couple other videos of a disc like ufo over last few days that was extremely bright and moving rapidly in one place. like an energy force was helping it hover and move in one area. but the energy force was moving very rapidly. i will post both videos. it never really stopped we just stopped recording after a while. although we do notice after the sun rises we no longer see anything. after seeing this ufo activity and doing much research. i don't know what to think or if i should worry. it's as if they know we are watching them. and i wonder why they would they want us to see them and why it seems to get more and more revealing as time goes on. i somewhat am afraid of not knowing what alien race it is or why they are there. and the safety of the human race and our planet concerns me. so to give myself some type of comfort i decided to give the information we have seen to mufon.
content.flightPath: Hovering then path,Path with directional change
content.summary: Seen many star like ufos hovering in sky. filmed one one phone and much more was revealed during filming of many ufos erratic hovering and flying and changing many colors. we see it all the time and decided to record it.

content.detailedDescription:
I am telling about this incident to see if anyone else may have seen a similar craft. as far as i know its the only one of this type of craft reported anyway this is what happened.
about 20 years ago myself wife and two children are driving home from a friends place in vancouver b.C. to our home in surrey b.C. a 30 min. drive. the route we took takes us right passed yvr our international airport as we drove passed we seen two planes land and that was it we were passed the airport. around 2 minutes later my wife who was driving the car southbound say's what the hell are these bright lights they are blinding me i cant see the road. i said it must be a plane landing but we were way past the airport just slow down and don't look at them and we will be ok, she is panicking saying she cant see anything. so i was in the passenger seat and i rolled down my window as fast as i could stuck my head way out the window and got a perfect view of this thing. it no longer had the bright lights on, there was also no navigation or beacon lights of any kind nor was there any sound or signs of propulsion. it was about 300 ft. off the ground and traveling approx.50 mph allot slower than the last 2 planes we just seen land. now comes the real strange part the bottom of this craft looked like it had 20ft by 10ft sheets of very thick black steel which were attached together by at least 2-4ft.Massive welds i have never seen anything with welds that big. i wanted to get some idea of the overall size of this thing but it fit so well into the dark sky it made it hard to see at all never mind judge the overall size. as it past over and you could sort of make out the back edge it was just as nuts it looked like it was just these super thick sheets of steel floating along. i asked my wife to stop the car so i could get a better look at it she replied with no f'n way in the world can you make me stop this car.
so i started to think what could this possibly be maybe there were heavy lift choppers but i would have noticed them for sure. i am a certified aerospace machinist by trade over the years built subs for the australian military, helicopters, planes for boeing and cessna. needless to say i know a man made air craft when i see one. the one we seen that night was possibly man made but not with human technology this thing looked evil it was not built for a pleasure cruise. i hate to admit it but it scared me also no matter who built it. 
we were so freaked out i even phoned the airport to see if something big or military came in.
the tower said nothing and gave a little giggle typical.

the reason i contacted you is i was wondering i you have had any other similar version to mine
content.summary: Driving with family in car ufo passed overhead

content.detailedDescription:
I was heading west/north west on highway/freeway 94 in between monticello, mn and clear water, mn.

i was initially driving the speed limit (70mph) when i noticed an incredibly bright object in the sky above the freeway. this light was white colored and so bright that it was flaring.

i attempted to take a picture while driving but it was dark out and i had to stay on the road. my phone camera wasn't picking up what i was observing with my own two eyes.

i had slowed down to about 50mph to get a good look at this thing. it took me about 1-3 minutes to get right under it while driving @50mph.

what i observed while passing right underneath it was triangular shaped with a bunch of small but bright blinking/pulsating led looking lights. there were 1 or 2 small solid red led looking lights. 

i continued to drive past it, still heading west/north west towards clear water, mn. i looked in my rear view mirror, and the white light was super bright and flaring again. 

this light completely surrounded the object, except underneath it, and possibly on top of it.

it was almost stationary, but when it would move it would move slowly and left a small trail behind it.
content.summary: Very bright white light. so bright it flared. white light completely surrounded object.

content.detailedDescription: This bright orb appears after dark, hovering low (i'd guess about a mile or less above ground)for hours. it is primarily glowing white with a little gold aura, and appears to flash red and blue lights. when looking through binoculars or telescope the image is blurry, moving, and sometimes appears to have a grid pattern over the surface of the object. when it is present there are planes and helicopters in the area, always maintaining a lower altitude and respectful circle of distance from the object. about a month ago a similar (the same?) object was seen over the longview bridge, about 5 miles from my house. it was after dark and the orb was hovering, clearly visible, just above the bridge, and there was a helicopter hovering close to my location facing in the direction of the orb, obviously observing it. sometimes it stays overnight, most of the time it is gone within a couple of hours.

content.detailedDescription:
I was driving home from work at 12:42 am and entered a clearing on the east river parkway bridge, when a very bright green orb streaked downward at the thorton place apartment building, the only 12 story building visible from that vantage point. the object looked to be on a collision course with the building but at the last minute leveled off and went behind the building (as i crested the top of the bridge) and down into the general area of hwy 94 like a tracer round shot out of a gun.
  there was no sound and the incident lasted all of 4-5 seconds.
  i am used to seeing helicopters in the area but this object was within 500 feet of me or about 4 blocks away and at the same height as a 12 story building.
 i have also observed shooting stars but they are always white in color and this was a very bright green, round and left a green trail behind it.
  most impressive to me is that it did not disintegrate in the atmosphere and it changed course at a very high rate of speed (similar to a tracer round fired down range at 800 meters), then tailed off as it continued to fall into the valley that is hwy 94 behind the building.
content.summary: Object seen while driving over bridge.Very bright headed straight for apartment tower then changed direction

content.detailedDescription: 4:26am observing stars and sky from my backyard.  facing north and looking at two stars slightly to the ne, i notice a strobe of light to the left of these two stars. i am wondering about that strobe when one of those two stars starts moving straight up away from the other one, then makes a gradual turn to the west and continues all the way, at the same speed,  to the southwest sky where it finally dimmed and i could no longer see it.  no blinking, no strobes, still at around 45-55 degrees above the horizon.    i turn back around to where i saw it begin (ne sky) to get my bearings on it’s starting point.   as i am looking at the one star remaining where i saw two just a minute before, then it starts to move also.   it begins by moving north, then it veers off on a gradual turn to the east and continues all the way to the south, past orion’s belt and disappears between orion's belt 3 stars and the bottom star of orion (rigel).  i spin back around facing north to where those two stars began their movement and stare at that spot.   again i see the strobe of light.   two seconds later the strobe of light appears just to the right (ne) of that original strobe.   again, about 5 seconds later i see a dimmer strobe of light even more to the right (ne) than the first one.   do not see any more strobes.    time back in house:  4:38am.
content.summary: Two star-like lights that moved off in opposite directions from one another, two minutes apart.

content.detailedDescription: today at 2:14 pm (beautiful, sunny day, slight breeze). i went out into my garage to take a break. i was sitting down looking out the window towards the east and saw an object heading from south to north. i stood up and immediately grabbed our binoculars that sit on the work bench just a few inches within arms reach. i tried to focus on the object through the open window with the binoculars but could not locate it, so i looked again out the window and saw that it was moving very quickly. i then ran about 7 or 8 steps out of the garage thinking i would get a better view. when i got outside it had totally disappeared. i called my husband and we looked around the skies to see if we could locate it, but were not able to. it was white in color with a fuzzy appearance. i believe that if i were to hold my thumb up to it, i would have been able to cover it. i probably was able to view it for a total of 6-7 seconds.
content.summary: White, rapid moving object during the day

content.detailedDescription: I was a guest at my parents house along with several family members at a backyard bbq in an outer borough of new york city in a highly populated area at around 7:11pm. my niece noticed the object while playing on a slide in the yard outside. she informed us all and i along with my father, mother, wife, 2 nieces and my 3 very small children watched it glide over us in a straight path across the sky. it was fairly low, silent, and reflected light or had some lights on it (not quite sure). at first i thought it was a balloon or drone which still may be the case although it doesn't look like any drone i've seen on the internet. the object seem to have appendages somewhat and the company i was with joked about it looking like a man in a jet pack. so it seemed to have blinking lights or may have been reflecting sunlight off of a metallic like surface. my father who has a somewhat professional nikon camera ran in the house to grab his camera and take photos. he was able to zoom in and snap a few photos with his camera as i recorded video of the object from my iphone. it acted somewhat like a balloon floating by since it never really slowed down, changed direction or speed, or strayed from its path.The bbq location was approximately 100-150 ft from interstate 95. the object seemed to travel in the southbound direction of the interstate and seemed to be directly above it. i started to think it was a drone at that point, possibly trying to get an arial perspective of the highway. we were all excited at the thought of it being a ufo/drone because being a new yorker, we have never really seen anything like that before. it was also a little disturbing to think maybe it was a drone recording is from above, just kinda creepy i guess. so i studied the video i have on my phone for a few minutes after the sighting and pondered what the object could be. i was pretty much settled on the thought of it being a drone until my father showed me the zoomed up image that he had taken in his camera (nikon) which is unidentifiable to me as a drone. i took a snapshot of his computer screen after he uploaded his camera pics to his computer. so the video i will post is from my iphone and the pixelated pic is from my fathers computer. he has the original pic which i'm sure is better quality to whomever may need it. settled on the thought of it being a drone at the time of recording, i gave up before it passed out of sight over the neighbors houses down the street. several minutes later i saw maybe 20-30 large white (weather balloon like ) balloons float past in the aky in similar direction.  they looked nothing like the first object we spotted. they seemed to be at a higher altitude and very spread apart. they were white and much harder to see and disappeared just the same in a similar direction but not exact direction of the first object.
content.summary: Noticed during a backyard bbq. quietly passed over in straight path, several witnesses, cell phone video and pics along with cell snapshot of computer screen from another's witnesses digital camera

content.detailedDescription: At 10:15 to 10:30 pm i was leaving an evening meeting in rural housing neighborhood about 3 miles west of sequim, wa.(48.8701, -123.16204) it was a clear night, and i was enjoying looking at the bright stars, driving on a rural road, when i spotted an orange star. i thought it was kinda neat, and i had never seen an orange star before. as i pulled up to the stop sign i got out looked at it for a couple minutes. there were other stars in the vicinity, but they were white, so it wasn't orange due to smoke or clouds. it looked like a star, but then i saw it seemed closer, like within lower earth orbit, since it was five to ten times larger than other stars in the sky. it did not blink or wink, like with atmospheric interference. it did not have any navigational lights on, nor wobble like a helicopter (which i saw later in the evening). compared to the helicopter, it was bigger, stable, silent, glowing and orange (not small, moving, noisy, blinking red, white, and green). when i used reference points, i felt it was not as far as the hill 2-4 miles to the south,southwest (ssw) of me. it seemed it was just hovering over the subdivision area around olson road and cassidy creek or aldercreek roads. i tried to take some photos, but it was too dim to be recorded. as a car was coming, i got in my car and drove. almost immediately i could not see it, as it was above me, and blanked out by my roof (i did not think to open the sun roof). i continued south and west via mill road to highway 101, which was about a half mile away. after 3ish minutes, i stopped at a gas station at the intersection and gassed up, but could not see it anymore. don't know if it moved, blinked out, or was drowned out by light pollution of the gas station. posting this record, in case someone else saw it, and can plot some kind of movement. it did not seem like a natural phenomenon. what are these orbs made of? they just seem as uniform light, not shadowed by any form.
content.summary: Orange orb hovering above sequim, wa suburb.

content.detailedDescription:
Was filming the organ mountain range mid-morning in may 2011.  noticed a disc or elongated object streak diagonally from ne to e and disappear behind the organ mountain range.  had to slow the video down frame by frame to get the image to show.  must have been traveling very fast due to the frame rate shown in the video.  there were no noises or booms to indicate missile testing which happens from time to time.  there is a military testing facility on the other side of the mountain range.  white sands.
usually we can hear the distant booms of ordinance being tested when they do that though.  my first thought it was a bug flying by quickly but after looking over and over at the video the object seems to disappear behind the mountains indicating it was a large object?

please see the video attached.
content.summary: Slim object, possibly disc shaped swooped downward very very quickly and dissappeared behind mountain range

content.detailedDescription:
I was downstairs and my wife called me up wanting me to take a look at something. we had moved the baby crib from the far end of or loft to an area near the vent closer to or bed due to the winter cold, an are with more light. what i saw was not a ufo but an imprint of an alien face on our daughters crib, it looked like it was made with my wife's makeup, it had a pinkish color and was waxy to the touch. i've personally experienced missing time, my father and mother also have had similar one time experiences that they recall, so i wasn't terrified, but my wife was certainly terrified. i felt like the impression was left purposefully for a reason that i can't pin down. we did our best to clean it off, feeling having it on the crib was unacceptable and creepy to both of us, we just wiped it down with tissue paper and are willing to have the crib tested as it hasn't been chemically cleaned. we tried to duplicate the mark, pressing our faces against different slats of the crib, grabbing them in different ways, we couldn't reproduce the skin texture or really anything that came close to what was a distinctly clear face that pressed into the slats, as if one eye was peering into our crib, the date and time are not ascertainable, we just happened to find it after moving the crib, our daughter was almost one year old on the date i have reported, the date we found it. it didn't come out of the box like that.. 

i have several photos using a sony nex 5 or 5n that are very clear and, well, creepy.  

i would like to talk to an investigator about all of my families past experiences, i would also like to know if anything like this has been reported, if there are similar pictures, etcetera. i would like feedback on what i'm seeing here, what would the face have looked like...
content.summary: The impression of an alien face on baby crib in pinkish waxy material

content.detailedDescription:
I was driving home from work, urbana md, using i-70. before i came upon the manassas exit i witnessed a whole cluster of blinking odd lights. i watched them for about a half a minute, trying to see first if they were airplanes but they seemed to be too close together and at equal distant from each other, and if they were planes they would have crashed into one another. some rocked back and forth, others stayed very bright. also, if they were a plane they'd have  white solid light with red and blue blinking lights, they did not. they dimmed out and they sky was completely clear in the exact same spot they all had been seconds before. 

driving down i-70 i kept seeing more and more odd lights. i stared at one during a straight stretch of the road near the libson exit and it stayed still until a plane started to come into view and it blinked once before completely disappearing. 

once i arrived onto route 100 i saw something that may have been a flair, but i'm not completely sure. there were no planes in the area, nor a military base for twenty or so miles out. it looked like a first a hovering bright white/purple dot. it started to fall, then rise back up, zigzag crazily whilst blinking so there was no constant light as it moved. if it were a flare, i'm not sure how it moved back up the sky, but it was very odd. a plane started to come into view and it completely disappeared. 

there are many military bases in the area, bwi airport, and we are in the flight zone for if the president is evacuated to camp david, we would see their planes/helicopters when used. it was an extremely odd night seeing so many ufo's, but with supposed upcoming events, it seemed very off but not at the same time.
content.summary: I don't really know..

content.detailedDescription:
I was heading east on the newburgh beacon bridge when i noticed three solid white lights in the distance. as i got closer i could see the shape of the craft, it was triangular with a white light on each corner. i also noticed it was moving extremely slow, almost hovering in place. after i got through the toll booth i could see the bottom of the craft and the blinking red light on top. the bottom had greyish jagged strips on it. it was absolutely a triangle, there was no tail to the craft, it made no noise and was basicaly motionless. at first i thought it might have been a military craft because stewart airforce base is close to the bridge but after getting such an incredible look at it and the fact it was hovering i have no idea what it could be.
it was at a very low altitude as well maybe around 500 feet and it made no sound at all. i wish i could have taken a picture but i was in traffic and could not stop.
content.summary: Three white lights, one in front one one each back corner, red blinking light on top.

content.detailedDescription: I just got off work got out of my truck and noticed something up above me and wasn't sure what it was, first i thought it might be balloons .Note it was 4:35 am clear night (the day before it rained in california this year), i watched the four very bright yellow orange lights. the object appeared to just stay in one position, as if it were watching me. strange feeling for maybe 10 mins. or more. i took a few pictures and a short video of this thing , i wasn't sure but i think i was actually viewing a ufo. it made no noise, it was a very quite morning, so i know it wasn't a plane or helicopter. i was standing watching this thing in awe. i had chills from the top of my head down my spine to the bottom of my heels very strange feeling. i watched this thing then it turned in a south eastern ward direction very slowly so i figured it would be moving away from me. so i got into my truck, shut the door and briefly turned away from it and looked to insert my key in my truck ignition then when i looked back at this thing it was completely gone, vanished. i turned off my truck stepped out again and it was no where to be seen, now this was all in just seconds of me getting in my truck??? i got out walked around for another 10 minutes or so and saw nothing. it was completely gone? i've never been a believer of ufo's but after this incidence i do believe we are not alone!!! i went home and woke my girlfriend and told her about what i had witnessed.
content.summary: 4 bright lights witnessed on a silent night

content.detailedDescription: I was driving home from marquette to gladstone while going south on u.S. 41 towards rapid river when i witnessed 2 fireballs descending in the sky approximately 10 minutes apart. the first one went across while the other descended straight down below tree-line. these were very large in size and extremely luminous .The first one dissipated and the second one descended down into tree line in south east area of sky towards rapid river/gladstone.The weather conditions were extremely clear.
content.summary: Traveling south on hwy 41 in rapid river in upper peninsula i saw 2 bright fireballs descending from the sky that were 10 minutes apart at approximately 1:45 am

content.detailedDescription:
September 20, 2015  ~9:00pm
wsw at about 20 degrees over the horizon, just below arcturus, i noticed an orange/white light.  it was brighter than arcturus.  over the span of a few minutes, it appeared to gain a bit of altitude and travel slight south.  the light exhibited a few slow strobing, shifting slight back and forth between orange and white without fully becoming either, as opposed to the twinkle of stars.

i ran for the binoculars, hoping to see some definition.  the binoculars were out of adjustment.  in the minute it took to properly adjust them, the light had disappeared.  i did not witness the disappearance, but had a clear enough view that i am fairly confident an aircraft would not have exited my field of view that quickly.
content.summary: Pulsing orange/white sphere

content.detailedDescription: While out watching for a iridium flare by a satellite pass expected in the northern sky when i saw a very bright flash not associated with the flare and much larger. the sky was very clear without any clouds making the direction of view unobscured. the size was distinctly larger than any usual star or satellite and did not appear to be similar to any aircraft. there was no visible indication before or after the bright light which would have indicated an aircraft. it lasted only a moment and did not move, just suddenly appeared then vanished. there were no aircraft in the immediate area which it occurred, though some in both a western and eastern direction as it typical. this occurred only approximately 1-2 days from a falling star observed in the north east direction from the same viewing location which i didn't think of at the time as being more than a lucky spotting of a falling star.
content.summary: Large very bright light appeard then vanished.

content.detailedDescription: I was truck driving on i-74 east and got ramp to go hwy 63 south.  while on the ramp, i saw red ball of light.  while heading south, the red turned white, and got smaller in size.  then, noticed that there was more than one and they were horseshoe shaped.  at times, they had red or green streaks shooting out of them!  after a couple of hours and a few pictures,  the sun came up and it was all over.
content.summary: Horseshoe shaped light and sometime shooting out red or green light from it.

content.detailedDescription: I was in my backyard in toledo, ohio, at approximately 1:00 p.M., est, watching my dog chase squirrels.  she was looking up at a squirrel on a telephone pole and i looked up at the sky.  i saw a white orb at what appeared to be a very far-off distance that seemed slightly reflective or metallic.  it was so far away, i thought it perhaps was a very large bird for a moment.  it was making a smooth, circular path at first.  within a second or so of me observing it, it changed directions very suddenly and was making sharp turns, no longer smooth motions.  this caught my attention and i don't think i blinked for the next minute.  the shape never changed or morphed, remaining a solid circle or sphere.  as i watched this, there were suddenly at least over a dozen white orbs.  they appeared out of nowhere and were just there.  there were too many to count in the very short time they were there.  as soon as i tried to count them, there were only three white orbs.  the three seemed to be flying in an easterly direction and then disappeared very quickly.  the whole sighting was probably less than a minute.   the weather was warm and very sunny, clear sky with only a few clouds.  they disappeared so quickly, i had no time to react to the sighting to run inside and grab a camera or anything.  my eyes were burning from not blinking and i really don't know what i saw.
content.flightPath: Hovering then path,Path with directional change
content.summary: Orbs over toledo
